    <title>INPORTD</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>page INPORTD INPORTD Function <programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">X<sp/>=<sp/>INPORTD(port)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Reads a <bold>32-bit double-word</bold> from <computeroutput>port</computeroutput> and returns it.</para>
<para><blockquote><para>[!IMPORTANT] Only use on devices that specify <bold>double-word</bold> port access. </para>
</blockquote></para>
<sect2 id="md_docpages_basic_language_reference_functions_integer_INPORTD_1autotoc_md67">
<title>&lt;/blockquote&gt;</title>
<sect3 id="md_docpages_basic_language_reference_functions_integer_INPORTD_1autotoc_md68">
<title>How to read it</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Reads four consecutive bytes from the port as a 32-bit value.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Common for PCI configuration space.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="md_docpages_basic_language_reference_functions_integer_INPORTD_1autotoc_md70">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Read<sp/>PCI<sp/>config<sp/>data</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">D<sp/>=<sp/>INPORTD(&amp;CFC)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>D</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="md_docpages_basic_language_reference_functions_integer_INPORTD_1autotoc_md72">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Most modern devices prefer MMIO; only use when the hardware requires 32-bit port access.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
